Description: Fragment of a pottery amphora (?); strap handle with small part of shoulder; handle decorated on outside with three pairs of red/brown horizontal stripes; one vertical stripe beside handle on shoulder. Hard, fine, orange clay with darker core, Munsell 5YR 6/4 (light reddish brown); silver mica.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 324)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
